="https://i.imgur.com/C6IkRQ5.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>But Don't</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/trkAZ4K</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[BlueVoter]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I am wobbly.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/SU15qYr</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/CUTrinY.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/SU15qYr</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[zakiamon]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>You’re truly one in a melon…</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/jJO1Igk</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/GbkF5UD.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/jJO1Igk</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[tractorist]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Out, damned uterus!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/BmySWYn</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/yxJ3mT1.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>My uterus is evil. It has been torturing me for years. I will have a relatively normal period. Followed by no periods for three months. Followed by a three week period. They're erratic and all over the place for at least three years</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/3KOpEMs.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>When I do have them, they're super heavy, super painful, and I'm freaking miserable. I used to be able to work through periods. Now I need to take time off on my worst days because I am in so much pain and cannot think.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/nfMvO85.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>A few years ago I TRIED to figure out what was going on but had a HORRIBLE experience. I was scheduled for a pap, ultrasound and biopsy to see what was going on and determine if I was a candidate for ablation (burning out the lining).

The day of the procedures, I found out they forgot to schedule the ultrasound. They didn't numb me, abraded my cervix so I bled for hours, when I asked why the biopsy was necessary, they answered "Cancer," when they meant "To rule out cancer," scraped me and I was in so freaking much pain. THEN they tried to squeeze me in for an ultrasound. I declined and never went back.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Dswuq4y.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>A month ago I talked about my experience with my sister. She empathized with my experience and encouraged my to find another doctor. 

Then I talked to a friend who had a similar traumatic experience and she referred me to someone she had finally had a good experience with. 

I called them and left a message. They called back immediately and apologized that they could only get me in the next week. They suggested a consult appointment BEFORE my annual. The doc was HORRIFIED at my story. She said the biopsy should never have happened based on my history of completely normal paps.

She mentioned the possibility of a hysterectomy, scheduled me for an ultrasound and pap and promised NO biopsy unless absolutely necessary.

Today I had my ultrasound. Uncomfortable as always, but...</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ndnArDA.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Answers! Progress! Doctors who listen, communicate, explain, and don't discount what you're going through! 

After today's ultrasound:

Note from {redacted}

"Hi {redacted}- the uterus is showing adenomyosis which is when the uterus is enlarged and the endometrial lining spreads to the muscle causing heavier more painful periods. Ovaries are normal. We can definitely get your scheduled for surgical consult for hysterectomy at your annual exam."

Yessssssssssssssssssss!

Get this fucking thing outta me!

Sorry, not sorry for TMI. Women do not have enough women to talk to about this shit. We are shamed into NOT talking about it with other women. 

Fuck. That. Noise.

Edit: thanks for the overwhelming response. I have never felt so heard and supported. Men and women alike. I love that we have so many male advocates. I'm sorry that so many women have or are experiencing similar trauma. These are our frigging bodies. Let's take back our power.

Second edit: if anyone is in Tucson, AZ and wondering, GENESIS OBGYN on Carondelet Dr. https://genesisobgyn.net/</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/BmySWYn</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[bchbum6]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>The patient listens very carefully to the doctor's recommendations</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/2aLTznE</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/BSZcqrx.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/2aLTznE</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Offernedis]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Ack!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/OTDALXQ</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/5CkACY4.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/OTDALXQ</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Newitt]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Stop</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Vwf17jV</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/TWSjhAb.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Vwf17jV</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[malbec]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Brennan for the win</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/q9nHV91</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/aET6ajJ.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/q9nHV91</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[AgentDoggit83]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>This is fantastic! Should be everywhere!!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/kIGlD0h</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Xhl5lI3.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/6hbcHJV.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span><