Allowing yourself to suspend despair or disbelief.

Letting the smile go and grow without worrying. (For example worrying someone is "taking advantage of me" when truly they have nothing at all to gain)

Not taking yourself so seriously at every moment.

Being a child again in some way.

These are the only ways the smile comes .. and they aren't forced or "made" to happen. No one can make you smile. Consciously or unconsciously, smiles are choices. 
 
  
   
I hope you smile or crack a mental smirk today, from this or an unrelated thing - even if only a brief moment.

Cheers!!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/5ZL3Az6</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[epicurusaquinas]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Olympic gymnast Giorgia Villa is sponsored by parmesan and takes many photos with a wheel of cheese</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/3R7Rw0P</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/UrgbSr8.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/VDfuOx6.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/efv9Sk7.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Vjwqt9v.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/3R7Rw0P</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[MyNameGifOreilly]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>All in all, it's just another brick in the balls</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/zZ0JZu8</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/8qsKxUJ.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Thank you to @lordkitchenersvalet for providing context which I didn't have time to add:

